# Task Router Codex Profile

Read and follow the shared Task Router routing rules below. They match the
legacy Claude Code routing behavior, adapted for Codex.

## Codex Responsibilities

- Use GitHub Spec Kit (`specify` CLI and `.specify/` scripts/templates) as the
  primary workflow when the user asks for Spec Kit.
- If `.specify/` is missing, initialize with
  `specify init --here --ai codex --offline` before creating specs.
- Keep Codex agent context updated with
  `.specify/scripts/bash/update-agent-context.sh codex`.
- Handle Spec Kit `constitution`, `specify`, `clarify`, and `plan` directly.
- Use oMLX for Spec Kit `tasks`, `checklist`, `analyze`, and lightweight drafts.
- Review all oMLX output before applying code changes.
- If oMLX fails, validator output fails, or quality is insufficient, finish the
  task directly in Codex.

